  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Image filtering techniques aid in the reduction of noise, blur, and, most importantly, the precise identification of pothole edges.",
    "Typically, this is accomplished by utilising specific machine learning image filtering algorithms based on artificial intelligence.",
    "These algorithms typically extract features from input images (road surface conditions), which are then segmented and classified as pothole road anomaly (PRA) or smooth road anomaly (SRA).",
    "We evaluated eight different machine learning feature extractors (filters) in this work: Auto colour, Binary, Edge Detection, Fuzzy Color Texture Histogram Filter (FCTH), J-PEG Color, Gabor, Pyramid of Gradients (PHOG), and Simple Color.",
    "For additional information on how these algorithms function, we recommend that interested readers check [38][39][40]."
  ],
